<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Is_a_terse_invocation_of_WP:TAGS_an_indicator_of_Good_Faith_discussion.3F">Is a terse invocation of WP:TAGS an indicator of Good Faith discussion?</span></h2>

<p>I am being met with a barrage of WP:TAGS that seem to border on <a href="" title="WP:PS">WP:PS</a>. Every time I try to address one, it becomes another, when I try get outside opinion regarding the applicability of <a href="" title="WP:RS">WP:RS</a>, <a href="" title="WP:NPOV">WP:NPOV</a>, <a href="" title="WP:OR">WP:OR</a> I am accused of forum shopping. When I explain that I feel that they are in the wrong and try to explain why while soliciting their thoughts I am accused of <a href="" title="WP:SOAP">WP:SOAP</a>, <a href="" title="WP:FORUM">WP:FORUM</a> and <a href="" title="WP:DE">WP:DE</a>. I am trying to assume good faith but I am halfway to <a href="" title="WP:NOCLUE">WP:NOCLUE</a>.  Please note that this is a general, necessarily POV assessment of what I feel transpired. We can go rummaging through the dirty laundry later. 
